Description: Sherd of wall of East Greek pottery bowl or cup; interior glazed with traces of added red bands; exterior, broad reserved band between orange-red fired areas; incised inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Gardner 1888 / Naukratis II (p. 66, no. 814b, pl. XXI, no. 814b)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.385)
